--- !u!114 &1694952199
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1694952198}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 69cb02f68621c7f41af9bda4ed48d0a9, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::LoreManager
  tape1:
    title: Tape 1
    content: "\u201C\u2026testing\u2014okay, it\u2019s recording.\r\n\r\nI don\u2019t
      know who this is for. Maybe for whoever wakes up next. If that even\u2026 works
      again.\r\n\r\nThe systems keep resetting, but not everything goes back the
      same. I checked the logs\u2014there are gaps. Entire sections just\u2026 gone.
      Or overwritten.\r\n\r\nThe Core\u2019s still active. It has to be.\r\n\r\nIf
      you\u2019re hearing this, just follow the instructions. Set up defenses. Don\u2019t
      question it too much.\r\n\r\nI tried that already.\u201D\r\n\r\n\u2026\u2026\r\n\r\n\u2026\u2026\r\n"
    icon: {fileID: 0}
  tape2:
    title: Tape 2
    content: "\u201C\u2026they told us the intruders were external.\r\n\r\nThat\u2019s
      what the protocol says.\r\n\r\nBut I\u2019ve been watching the feeds, and\u2026
      they don\u2019t come from \u25A1\u25A1\u25A1\r\n\r\nIt\u2019s like they \u25A1\u25A1\u25A1
      where there wasn\u2019t anything before. No breach. No entry point.\r\n\r\nJust\u2026
      there.\r\n\r\nMaybe the defenses aren\u2019t keeping them out.\r\n\r\nMaybe
      they\u2019re keeping something \u25A1\u25A1\u25A1.\u201D\r\n\r\n\u2026\u2026\r\n\r\n\u201COr
      keeping us where we\u2019re suptojkefvjewGDFVWIEI\u25A1\u25A1\u25A1\u25A1\u25A1\u25A1\u25A1\u25A1\u25A1\u25A1\u25A1\u201D\r\n\r\n\u2026\u2026\r\n"
    icon: {fileID: 0}
  tape3:
    title: Tape 3
    content: "\u201C\u2026I finally reached the Core chamber.\r\n\r\nIt\u2019s not
      damaged. Not even close. Everything we\u2019ve been doing\u2014defending, repairing\u2014it
      doesn\u2019t look like it\u2019s ever been touched.\r\n\r\nI thought maybe
      we were too late, or too early, but\u2026\r\n\r\nNo. That\u2019s not it.\r\n\r\nIt\u2019s
      like it doesn\u2019t need protection.\u201D\r\n\r\n\u2026\u2026\r\n\r\n\u201CI
      saw my reflection on the surface.\r\n\r\nIt didn\u2019t\u2026 move when I did.\u201D\r\n\r\n\u2026\u2026\r\n\r\n\u201C\u2026I
      don\u2019t think that was me.\u201D\r\n\r\n\u2026\u2026\r\n"
    icon: {fileID: 0}
  document1:
    title: Internal Memorandum (Summary)
    content: 'Recent observations indicate irregular system behavior within the facility.
      Several automated processes have activated without logged authorization, though
      no direct faults have been identified. Personnel are advised to continue standard
      operations and avoid unnecessary interaction with restricted components, including
      the Core. No external communication regarding these anomalies is permitted
      until further review is completed.

'
    icon: {fileID: 0}
  document2:
    title: Security Notice (Summary)
    content: All staff are reminded that access to designated sectors remains limited
      under current protocol. Reports of unidentified movement within secured areas
      have not been substantiated; however, standard defensive measures are to remain
      active at all times. In the event of intrusion, priority is to prevent approach
      to the Core. Additional resources should be allocated as necessary.
    icon: {fileID: 0}
  document3:
    title: 'Emergency Directive (Summary) '
    content: If containment integrity is compromised, all available resources must
      be redirected to Core protection. Do not attempt evacuation unless explicitly
      authorized. Previous instructions may no longer apply under current conditions.
      Maintain defensive systems and respond to threats as they appear. Further guidance
      will be issued if communication remains stable.
    icon: {fileID: 0}
  newspaper1:
    title: Infrastructure Advisory Notice
    content: City officials have acknowledged ongoing concerns regarding intermittent
      siren activity reported across several districts over the past month. According
      to a formal statement released earlier this week, the sounds are attributed
      to routine testing procedures linked to a secured underground installation.
      While authorities maintain that these operations pose no risk to the public,
      independent experts have noted irregular intervals and durations inconsistent
      with standard testing protocols. Residents have also reported brief lapses
      in communication networks coinciding with the sirens. Requests for further
      clarification have not been addressed. Officials continue to advise the public
      to disregard the disturbances and avoid restricted access points.
    icon: {fileID: 0}
  newspaper2:
    title: Unverified Reports Prompt Inquiry
    content: An internal review has been requested following multiple unverified
      accounts from personnel associated with a privately managed research site.
      Sources, speaking under condition of anonymity, describe inconsistencies in
      recorded activity logs and cite instances of systems operating without direct
      input. While no official confirmation has been issued, documentation reviewed
      by this publication suggests that several scheduled procedures were either
      repeated or initiated outside of designated timeframes. Oversight committees
      have declined to comment on whether these anomalies indicate technical malfunction
      or administrative error. The organization maintains that all systems remain
      within operational parameters.
    icon: {fileID: 0}
  newspaper3:
    title: Restricted Zone Expansion
    content: Authorities have extended the boundaries of a previously designated
      restricted zone, citing updated safety protocols. Access to the area is now
      limited to authorized personnel only, with checkpoints established along all
      major entry routes. Officials have not disclosed the specific nature of the
      revision but emphasize that the decision was made as a precautionary measure.
      Residents in adjacent sectors have reported an unusual absence of typical industrial
      noise from the site, accompanied by occasional low-frequency vibrations. Despite
      inquiries from local representatives, no additional details have been released.
      The restriction is expected to remain in place indefinitely.
    icon: {fileID: 0}
  journal:
    title: XX-XX-XXXX
    content: "I woke up again today.\r\n\r\nI think it was morning. There\u2019s
      no way to tell down here, but the lights were dimmer than usual. Or maybe I
      just remember them being brighter.\r\n\r\nI found another note in the hallway.
      Same handwriting. Same message about protecting the Core. I don\u2019t remember
      writing it, but it feels familiar. Like something I\u2019ve already decided.\r\n\r\nThe
      bunker feels\u2026 different. Not empty\u2014just rearranged. Doors I\u2019m
      sure were open are closed now. Some paths don\u2019t lead where they used to.
      I tried marking the walls, but the markings don\u2019t stay.\r\n\r\nOr they
      move.\r\n\r\nI haven\u2019t seen anyone else, but I don\u2019t feel alone.
      Sometimes I hear something behind me, but when I turn, it\u2019s gone. Not
      gone\u2014just\u2026 not there anymore.\r\n\r\nThe Core is still active. It
      always is.\r\n\r\nI stood in front of it for a while today. I thought I saw
      something in the reflection, but it didn\u2019t last long enough to understand.\r\n\r\nI
      don\u2019t know how long I\u2019ve been here.\r\n\r\nBut I\u2019m starting
      to think leaving was never the point.\r\n"
    icon: {fileID: 0}
  detailPanel: {fileID: 200188278}
  detailIcon: {fileID: 0}
  detailTitle: {fileID: 1774571195}
  detailContent: {fileID: 716433574}
  closeButton: {fileID: 1877416373}
